st status-publish format-standard hentry category-elo-ratings category-anal=
ytics">
	<header class=3D"entry-header">
		<h1 class=3D"entry-title">What are Elo Ratings and How do they Work?</h1>=
			<div class=3D"entry-meta">
				<span class=3D"post-author-wrapper">
					By DubStat on				</span>
				<span class=3D"posted-on"><a href=3D"https://dubstat.com/what-are-elo-r=
atings-and-how-do-they-work/" rel=3D"bookmark"><time class=3D"entry-date pu=
blished" datetime=3D"2023-05-12T20:33:41-04:00">May 12, 2023</time><time cl=
ass=3D"updated" datetime=3D"2024-08-22T19:30:42-04:00">August 22, 2024</tim=
e></a></span><span class=3D"byline"> </span>			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
				</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	<div class=3D"entry-content">
	=09
<hr class=3D"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity">



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading">What are Elo Ratings?</h2>



<p class=3D"">Elo ratings are a way to measure the relative skill of player=
s or teams in zero sum games (where each competitor either wins or loses). =
</p>



<p class=3D"">Elo ratings are a way to rank players or teams mathematically=
 using a fairly simple algorithm. They are historically the most accurate w=
ay to rank a large number of competitors without human input. </p>



<hr class=3D"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity">



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center">Arpad Elo</h2>


<div class=3D"wp-block-image">
<figure class=3D"aligncenter size-full is-resized"><img fetchpriority=3D"hi=
gh" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"246" height=3D"292" src=3D"https://dubstat.=
com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-4.png" alt=3D"What are Elo ratings - A=
rpad Elo" class=3D"wp-image-1405" style=3D"width:298px;height:auto"></figur=
e>
</div>


<p class=3D""></p>



<p class=3D"">The Elo system is named after its creator, Arpad Elo, a physi=
cs professor and chess player, who first created the system to be used in c=
hess tournaments in the 1960s.</p>



<p class=3D"">The Elo system has since been adapted for use in other games =
and sports such as boxing, wrestling, football, baseball, and basketball.</=
p>



<hr class=3D"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity">



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center has-cyan-bluish-gray-co=
lor has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-68d0f9ce101fdd4428047a567a45a=
859">Related Articles</h2>



<p class=3D""><a href=3D"https://dubstat.com/how-does-dubstat-calculate-foo=
tball-elo-ratings/" data-type=3D"post" data-id=3D"5582">How does DubStat ca=
lculate Elo ratings?</a></p>



<p class=3D""><a href=3D"https://dubstat.com/elo-ratings-the-ultimate-sport=
s-ranking-system/" data-type=3D"post" data-id=3D"5573">Elo Ratings: The Ult=
imate Sports Ranking System</a></p>



<hr class=3D"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity">



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center">How do Elo ratings wor=
k?</h2>



<p class=3D"">The Elo system works by assigning each player an initial Elo =
rating (typically <code>1,000 or 1,500</code>). This number represents the =
player=E2=80=99s relative skill level and will be adjusted with each game t=
hey play.</p>



<p class=3D"">When two players compete against each other, the player with =
the higher Elo rating is more likely to win.</p>



<hr class=3D"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity">



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center">An Example</h2>



<p class=3D"">For example, if <strong>Player A </strong>has an Elo rating o=
f <strong>1500</strong> and <strong>Player B </strong>has an Elo rating of =
<strong>1400</strong>, then <strong>Player A is expected to win</strong> th=
e game.</p>



<p class=3D"">The difference in player ratings will determine how many poin=
ts are added or subtracted from each player at the end of the game.</p>



<p class=3D""><strong>If Player A wins</strong>, they will receive a small =
increase in their Elo rating, while Player B=E2=80=99s rating will decrease=
 by the same amount. Neither player=E2=80=99s Elo rating will change much b=
ecause the game went as expected.</p>



<p class=3D"">However,<strong> If Player B wins</strong> (was expected to l=
ose), they will receive a larger increase in their Elo rating, while Player=
 A will receive a larger decrease. This match did not go as expected, so th=
e system needs to make a larger correction.</p>



<hr class=3D"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity">



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center">Elo ratings are self-c=
orrecting</h2>



<p class=3D"">Over time, a player=E2=80=99s Elo rating will change as they =
win or lose games. If a player consistently performs well, their rating wil=
l increase, and if they consistently perform poorly, their rating will decr=
ease. </p>



<p class=3D"">This makes the Elo system a self-correcting system that conti=
nually adjusts to reflect the current skill level of each competitor.</p>



<hr class=3D"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity">



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center">Advantages of Elo Rati=
ngs</h2>



<p class=3D"">One of the greatest advantages of the Elo system is that it i=
s simple and easy to understand. The formula for calculating Elo ratings is=
 straightforward, and it can be adapted for use in many different games and=
 sports.</p>



<p class=3D"has-text-align-center has-small-font-size">(If you=E2=80=99re i=
nterested in the math behind Elo ratings, the entire Elo formula is at the =
bottom of the article)</p>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-pullquote" style=3D"border-width:8px;font-style:n=
ormal;font-weight:500"><blockquote><p>Elo ratings are now used to project o=
utcomes of online games such as =E2=80=9CGo=E2=80=9D (see <a href=3D"http:/=
/goratings.org/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer noopener">goratings.or=
g</a>), most major professional sports (see <a href=3D"http://fivethirtyeig=
ht.com/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer noopener">fivethirtyeight.com<=
/a>), and amateur wrestling (see <a href=3D"http://wrestlestat.com/" target=
=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer noopener">wrestlestat.com</a> and <a href=3D"=
https://dubstat.com/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer noopener">dubstat=
.com</a>)</p></blockquote></figure>



<p class=3D"">Another advantage is that the Elo system is based on the resu=
lts of actual competitions, which makes it an objective measure of skill th=
at is not impacted by emotion or human preference.</p>



<p class=3D"">Unlike manual rating systems, Elo ratings can be used to to c=
reate rankings for large numbers of competitors. Essentially, there is no l=
imit to how many competitors can be ranked using Elo ratings. In fact, Ches=
s.com has over 100 million users with each one receiving a rating.</p>



<p class=3D"">In addition, the Elo system can be used to match players of s=
imilar skill levels against each other, which makes for more competitive an=
d exciting games. </p>



<hr class=3D"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity">



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading">Conclusion</h2>



<p class=3D"">In summary, Elo ratings are a method of calculating the relat=
ive skill levels of players in two-player games. The system was developed b=
y Arpad Elo and has been adapted for use in many different games and sports=
. The Elo system is based on the results of actual games and is a simple an=
d objective measure of skill.</p>



<hr class=3D"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity">



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading">Elo Rating System</h2>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding=3D"async" width=3D=
"760" height=3D"364" src=3D"https://dubstat.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/=
image-125.png" alt=3D"What are elo ratings - Elo system" class=3D"wp-image-=
5245"></figure>

